Key Match Events: Yashasvi Jaiswal scored an unbeaten 93 runs.
India won by 10 wickets, taking an unassailable 3-1 lead in the series.
Shivam Dube and Abhishek Sharma performed commendably in the middle overs.
Tushar Deshpande made his debut and took the wicket of Sikandar Raza.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This is the second time that India beat Zimbabwe by 10 wickets at the same venue, the first being in 2016.
Zimbabwe's best opening stand for the series in the first three games was 9, but Madhevere and Marumani added 63 in this match.
